</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">
The order 
<taxonomicName class="Diplopoda" genus="Polyxenus" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="order">Glomerida</taxonomicName>
, according to published data, is represented by three genera in Slovakia - 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Heller" authorityYear="1858" class="Diplopoda" family="Pythiaceae" genus="Trachysphaera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Trachysphaera" order="Polyzoniida" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Trachysphaera</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Glomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glomeris" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Glomeris</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Verhoeff" authorityYear="1908" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Geoglomeris" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Geoglomeris" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">Geoglomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lang, J." journalOrPublisher="Ceskoslovenska Akademie Ved, Praha" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" refId="B7164795" refString="Lang, J., 1954. Mnohonozky - Diplopoda. Fauna CSR, 2. Ceskoslovenska Akademie Ved, Praha" title="Mnohonozky - Diplopoda. Fauna CSR, 2" year="1954">Lang 1954</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kime, R. D." journalOrPublisher="Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda)" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" refId="B7164722" refString="Kime, R. D., Enghoff, H., 2011. . Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda) Vol. 1" volume="Vol. 1" year="2011">Kime and Enghoff 2011</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kime, R. D." journalOrPublisher="Atlas of European millipedes (Class Diplopoda)" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" refId="B7164730" refString="Kime, R. D., Enghoff, H., 2013. Fauna Europaea: Diplopoda. In: Fauna Europaea version 2017.06." title="Fauna Europaea: Diplopoda" volumeTitle="Fauna Europaea version 2017.06." year="2013">Kime and Enghoff 2013</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Kocourek, P" journalOrPublisher="Cesky svaz ochrancu prirody Vlasim" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" refId="B7329953" refString="Kocourek, P, Tajovsky, K, Dolejs, P, 2017. Mnohonozky Ceske republiky. Prirucka pro urcovani nasich druhu. Cesky svaz ochrancu prirody Vlasim" title="Mnohonozky Ceske republiky. Prirucka pro urcovani nasich druhu" year="2017">Kocourek et al. 2017</bibRefCitation>
). Genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Glomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glomeris" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">Glomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rather problematic, as it represents a complex of species, characterised by inconsistency and unreliable determination information in the old literature. 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. tetrasticha" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" rank="species" species="tetrasticha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">G. tetrasticha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. hexasticha" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" rank="species" species="hexasticha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">G. hexasticha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. pustulata" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" rank="species" species="pustulata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">G. pustulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
represent well-confirmed species, occurring in the territory of Slovakia. Only one old record of 
<taxonomicName genus="G." lsidName="G. klugii" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">G. klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from Slovakia exists. In the area of Slovakia, some populations of the species of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1802" class="Diplopoda" family="Glomeridae" genus="Glomeris" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Glomeris" order="Glomerida" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="71495">Glomeris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are characterised by a remarkable variety of colouration, which could indicate the ongoing speciation processes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
